comment: Barnes (GSW) sets the screen on Harris (DEN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After Gallinari (DEN) sets a screen and gives Curry (GSW) the room to avoid the contact, the two players briefly engage and separate.
Gallinari (DEN) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact that does not affect Curry's (GSW) RSBQ on the drive and layup attempt.
RHH shows that Nelson's (DEN) right foot steps OOB on the baseline drive.
Thompson (GSW) maintains legal guarding position and Iguodala (GSW) cleanly strips the ball from Gallinari (DEN) on his driving layup attempt.
Gallinari (DEN) and Curry (GSW) make incidental contact with one another while diving for the loose ball.
Iguodala (GSW) commits a take foul on Harris (DEN).
Barnes (GSW) sets the screen on Nelson (DEN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Iguodala (GSW) commits a take foul on Gallinari (DEN).

Curry (GSW) signals for a timeout after Thompson (GSW) secures the ball, but it is not acknowledged by officials. The trail official acknowledges the timeout request from Golden State's head coach at the 0:01.8 mark after Thompson has already dribbled. Because Thompson dribbled prior to the timeout being granted, the clock should not have been reset and Golden State should not have had the option to advance the ball to the 28' hash mark upon resumption of play. The ball should have been inbounded on the sideline where play was interrupted with 0:01.8 remaining on the clock. Golden State should have had to request an additional timeout in order to advance the ball in this situation, but they did not have any timeouts remaining.
Mudiay (DEN) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
